  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Major geopolitical breakthrough with US-Iran direct talks led by VP Vance could resolve Strait of Hormuz tensions, causing oil to drop and reducing stagflation pressures. Bitcoin surged to $72K on peace optimism and potential regulatory clarity from the CLARITY Act, while capital rotation from BTC to ETH suggests risk-on sentiment within crypto markets.",
    "regimeImpact": "The bear market relief rally gains fundamental support from geopolitical de-escalation reducing oil-driven stagflation risks, but remains a relief rally until we reclaim SPY 200 SMA at 662.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Continue BMNR cash-secured put ladder as BTC holds above $62,300 structural level with peace talks providing upside catalyst",
      "Monitor oil prices closely - sustained drop below $100 removes stagflation constraint and could extend relief rally",
      "Prepare to reduce short book exposure if US-Iran deal materializes and Strait of Hormuz reopens as Trump indicated"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil dropping on US-Iran peace talks removes key stagflation pressure that has capped equity multiples.",
      "Bitcoin weekly MACD turning bullish at $72K suggests crypto leading risk-on rotation despite analyst skepticism on bottoming.",
      "Capital rotating from Bitcoin to Ethereum indicates broadening crypto appetite beyond safe-haven BTC positioning.",
      "CLARITY Act regulatory developments could unlock institutional crypto capital if passed alongside geopolitical stability."
    ]
